        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:44PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Hainesville to near
Longview. Movement was north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, White Oak, Gladewater, Gilmer, Mineola, Winnsboro,
Leesburg, Quitman, Lone Star, Big Sandy, Hawkins, Ore City,
Clarksville City, East Mountain, Scroggins, Pleasant Grove,
Hainesville, Diana, Rosewood, and Newsome.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
